nerated a #GP fault (which linux turns<br />into a segmentation fault), because the IDT entry for #2 would have been<br />marked as privileged - while the new page fault handler has no<br />reasonable way of finding out what's up... <br /><br />Perfecting the patch is going to take some time - the current one<br />essentially just fixes the lock-up. <br /><br />		Linus<br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
